EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 042300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO LIE 1003 IN N UTSIRE.
OVERNIGHT THIS LOW IS FCST TO LIE OVER CENTRAL SWEDEN BY MIDDAY ON SATURDAY.
IT WILL THEN CONTINUE TO MOV E ALLOWING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE TO TEMPO
FORM FOR SUNDAY. HOWEVER THIS WILL SOON DECLINE SEWARDS AS A SMALL LOW PRESSURE
IS LIKELY TO FORM OVER NERN SCOTLAND LATER ON SUNDAY AND MOV E TO LIE ACROSS
N CULLERCOATS FOR MONDAY. STRG OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE LIKELY AT FIRST
ON FRIDAY BUT SHOULD GRADUALLY EASE ACROSS WERN PARTS OVERNIGHT. NEAR GALE
FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO CONTINUE ACROSS THE E OF CULLERCOATS ON SATURDAY
WITH A RISK OF GALES. OVERNIGHT WINDS ARE FCST TO STEADILY EASE FM THE N.
ON SUNDAY FURTHER STRG OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE LIKELY TO SPREAD INTO
FAIR ISLE THESE ARE THEN FCST TO SPREAD E TO AFFECT THE N OF THE REGION
